				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For random accesses within the space HL has already set up, what's wrong with directly specifying values to L (or H for that matter) if the next element is further away than the nearest neighbor so single INC/DEC isn't enough ?<br />7 cycles for directly speficied element isn't bad if you cannot reach your goal in the next INC or DEC... still beats IX+x modes by several cycles (14 vs 19). You'll still have to put your stuff in 256 byte pages though, but that's not a limitation, and crossing the page would incur update to top part which can just be INC HL (6 cycles), and similar to page crossing penalty on 65x.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.tmeeco.eu">http://www.tmeeco.eu</a><!-- m --></div>
